e:["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4 text-slate-700 mb-10","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-slate-900","children":"VA payment date rule (deterministic):"}]," VA disability compensation is paid monthly, on the first business day of the following month. If the first day is a weekend or a U.S. federal holiday, payment is issued on the last business day before the first."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-slate-900","children":"Holiday handling:"}]," We apply U.S. federal holiday observance rules (holiday observed on Friday if it falls on Saturday; observed on Monday if it falls on Sunday). Payment dates are moved only backward (never forward) because the statute triggers a “preceding business day” adjustment."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-slate-900","children":"Provenance + verification:"}]," Each VA schedule page includes a statutory citation (38 U.S.C. §5120(e)–(f)) as the authoritative basis for timing logic, and a “Last verified” timestamp for governance. Rate/COLA pages cite VA.gov rate tables and link to the SSA COLA announcement that drives the annual adjustment."]}]]}]
